WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.830
A Pin on Image slide lets participants tap anywhere on a custom image to mark their answer.

2
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:08.270
Click New Presentation to start a fresh deck.

3
00:00:11.000 --> 00:00:15.130
Select Pin on Image from the Unscored section of the slide type picker.

4
00:00:16.000 --> 00:00:19.530
Type your spatial question — tell participants exactly what to pin.

5
00:00:22.000 --> 00:00:26.020
Click the image area to open the image library and choose a photo for your slide.

6
00:00:27.000 --> 00:00:29.740
Switch to the Stock Photos tab to search the library.

7
00:00:30.000 --> 00:00:34.490
Type a keyword to find the perfect photo — we're searching for a world map.

8
00:00:38.500 --> 00:00:40.120
Tap any result to select it.

9
00:00:42.500 --> 00:00:46.390
Adjust the crop if you like, then hit Save to add the world map to your slide.

10
00:00:46.500 --> 00:00:48.720
Your image is now saved to the slide.

11
00:00:52.000 --> 00:00:54.320
Click Preview to rehearse before going live.

12
00:00:56.500 --> 00:01:01.050
The participant screen shows your image. Your audience taps it on their phone to drop a pin.

13
00:01:01.500 --> 00:01:05.080
Responses appear on screen as each participant drops their pin.

14
00:01:05.500 --> 00:01:08.560
Pins appear live on the presenter screen as responses come in.

15
00:01:10.000 --> 00:01:12.270
Click the back arrow to return to the editor.

16
00:01:13.500 --> 00:01:16.320
That's all it takes. Hit Present when you're ready to go live.
